1 olive oil
1 Beef Rump
½ tin chickpeas
1 cucumber
1 tomato
1 packet salad leaves
1 packet Mustard Cider Dressing
1 packet Mango Mayonnaise
1 packet Roasted Peanuts & Cashew Mix
1 bag coriander
1 sachet Mumbai Spice Blend
1 sachet Indian spice blend
1 flatbreads

• Place beef between two sheets of baking paper. Pound with rolling pin until slightly flattened (this ensures it’s extra tender!)
• In a bowl, combine beef, Mumbai spice blend and a drizzle of olive oil
• Heat oil in a frying pan over high heat
• Cook beef for 5-6 mins or until cooked to your liking
• Transfer to a plate to rest.

• Drain chickpeas (1/2 tin for 2P/ 1 tin for 4P)
• Wipe out pan, return to medium-high heat with drizzle of oil. Add chickpeas and mild North Indian spice blend and toss until warmed through, 2 mins
• Return pan to medium-high heat. Drizzle flat breads with oil. Cook flatbreads (1 for 2P / 2 for 4P) until golden and warmed through, 1-2 mins each side
• Roughly chop cucumber and tomato.

• In a bowl, combine salad leaves, cucumber, tomato, dressing and drizzle of oil. Season
• Slice steak
• Plate up salad, chickpeas and steak
• Top with mayo, nuts and torn coriander
• Serve with flat breads.